<h2 id="section-top">Ophthalmology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1596">Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">-<br/>0114 2711900</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentdb54c8829c924098bfe7584296623095">
</div>
<p><strong>Ophthalmology</strong> is the study and treatment of eye diseases, injuries and disorders. Based almost entirely at the Royal Hallamshire Hospital, the department offers a range of regional, national and specialised services which include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Artificial eye service</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sheffieldeyecentre-nhs.uk/" target="_blank">Cataract surgery</a></li>
<li>Contact lens</li>
<li>Corneal</li>
<li>Diabetic Eye Screening Programme</li>
<li>Diagnostic services (including electro-diagnostics and Goldmann perimetry)</li>
<li>Emergency Eye Centre</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sth.nhs.uk/services/a-z-of-services?id=61&amp;page=493" target="_blank">Eye Clinic Liaison Officer</a></li>
<li>Glaucoma (screening, treatment and long-term management)</li>
<li>Intravitreal injections (Lucentis and Avastin)</li>
<li>Laser treatment and photo-dynamic therapy</li>
<li>Low vision aid service</li>
<li>Minor operations under local anaesthetic (for example, removal of cysts and chalazions)</li>
<li>Neuro-ophthalmology</li>
<li>Ocular oncology</li>
<li>Ocular-plastics</li>
<li>Orthoptics</li>
<li>Other general eye conditions/diseases</li>
<li>Paediatric clinics</li>
<li>Photography (including fluoresceins, angiography and orbital OCTs)</li>
<li>Retinal disease (including diabetes)</li>
<li>Retinal surgery</li>
<li>Squints</li>
<li>Uveitis</li>
</ul>
<p>In addition to its consultants, the department employs a variety of junior medical, nursing, technical, support and admin staff to assist in delivering a comprehensive eye care service to all its patients.</p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>Referral address<br/>Ophthalmology New Patient Referrals,<br/>Directorate of Ophthalmology,<br/>Royal Hallamshire Hospital,<br/>Sheffield,<br/>S10 2JF<br/><br/>Emergency Eye Clinic<br/>The Emergency Eye Clinic is open from 8:30am – 4:30pm - Monday to Friday.<br/><br/>Clinic times<br/>The Ophthalmology out-patient clinic is located on A-floor</p>
</div>
